SIMPLE: delineation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Delineation
<hw>De*lin`e*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>delineatio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧lin⟦eacute⟧ation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
representing, portraying, or describing, as by lines, diagrams,
sketches, etc.; drawing an outline; <as>as, the <ex>delineation</ex> of
a scene or face</as>; in drawing and engraving, representation by means
of lines, as distinguished from representation by means of tints and
shades; accurate and minute representation, as distinguished from art
that is careless of details, or subordinates them excessively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A delineated picture; representation; sketch;
description in words.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their softest <qex>delineations</qex> of female beauty.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Irving.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sketch; portrait; outline. See
<er>Sketch</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Delineator</ent>⟦br⟧
